<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She's got a heavy schedule on her plate as she prepares to direct two movies back to back.</p>

<p>But Olivia Wilde is making sure to treat herself to some R&amp;R as she juggles work with riasing two young children with partner Jason Sudeikis.</p>

<p>On Monday, the former House star, 36, was spotted once again enjoying a horseback riding session in the Los Angeles suburb of Thousand Oaks.</p>

<p>The great outdoors: Olivia Wilde enjoyed another horseback riding session in the LA suburb of Thousand Oaks on Monday as she took time for some R&amp;R</p>

<p>Wilde was dressed in a black tank top and black jodhpurs and boots for the session.</p>

<p>She wore black gloves and tucked her hair under a black helmet.</p>

<p>She has been spotted riding regularly as she and her family continue to reside in Southern California during the ongoing COVOD-19 pandemic.</p>

<p>They moved west when the coronavirus shut down New York City where they have a home.</p>

<p>Stylish equestrian: The actress and director, 36, opted for an all-black ensemble of tank top, jodhpurs, boots and gloves along with a safety helmet </p>

<p>In demand: The actress, who found fame on TV's House, garnered critical acclaim for her 2019 feature directorial debut Booksmart and has just been tapped to make a Marvel movie for Sony</p>

<p>In 2019, the actress made her feature directorial debut with the high school comedy Booksmart which garnered plenty of buzz and critical acclaim.</p>

<p>Next up, she's set to helm as well as star in the psychological thriller Don't Worry, Darling about an unhappy 1950s housewife.</p>

<p>And earlier this month, it was announced that Wilde has signed a deal to direct a Marvel movie for Sony Pictures which is believed to center on Spider-Woman.</p>

<p>The in demand star is also attached to direct an as-yet untitled holiday movie for Universal Pictures.</p>

<p>Couple: Wilde and partner Jason Sudeikis, who share two children, relocated from New York to the Los Angeles area to ride out the COVID-19 pandemic. They're pictured in December  </p>
